cast.overview: In a small town in Maine, seven children known as The Losers Club come face to face with life problems, bullies and a monster that takes the shape of a clown called Pennywise.
cast.title: It

details.biography:
James Magwood is an Indigenous actor from Toronto, Ontario, Canada. James began his acting journey in 2017 where he started doing background work for many feature films such as, It (2017). James has also had multiple supporting/starring roles in Feature Films! Since James was a young child he was always infatuated on how films were made. James would sit in front of the TV for hours watching behind the scenes footage instead of the actual film itself! This sparked an interest for James, he would go on to create many short films and stop motion animations and post them on YouTube. James always knew he wanted a career in the entertainment industry and continues to act, direct and even write. James is an active member of the ever growing acting community!

- IMDb Mini Biography By: Jessica Porterlance
